data.text:
About Philip Reinisch Company

The Philip Reinisch Company was established in 1932. Today, the company is the largest furniture company to manufacture curio cabinet accent pieces. Other product lines include related items like hall trees and consoles, as well as dining room furniture. The Philip Reinisch Company is focused on manufacturing furniture collections in the United States. They pride themselves on servicing their customers with quick shipment of all furniture items. Furniture items are created by skilled craftsmen from a German settlement in the US. The Color Time Collection is a grouping of accent pieces destined to become family heirlooms. These updated curio cabinets are available in striking, bold colors to add style to your home. The hall tree organizer features a functional design with plenty of storage and a padded bench. Double hooks are provided for hats and scarves. The outstanding chili pepper red color with a clear mirror finish adds a bold statement to an entrance hall. The new Color Time Caf groupings offer dining room sets in a variety of colors with matching curio cabinets. The elegant Lighthouse collection features a sturdy frame and elegant design in a corner curio cabinet. The cabinet provides traditional styling with double doors and a lighted interior with clear glass shelving. This cabinet is constructed of solid northern hardwood with a hand rubbed and polished candlelight cherry finish. The elegant Halo collection of curio cabinet accent pieces features master artist craftsmanship with meticulous attention to detail. Styling blends modern designs with classic influences to create a strikingly beautiful piece to enhance your home. These curio cabinets are made of solid northern hardwood with a hand carved wave design. Two way sliding glass doors add style and open to adjustable glass shelving and a mirrored back.
